thread.title_full: DIARY - Today in Washington - Aug 13 | Reuters

author: Reuters
title: DIARY - Today in Washington - Aug 13
text:
ALL TIMES IN EDT/GMT
0830/1230: The Labor Department issues weekly Jobless Claims; Import and Export Prices for July.
0830/1230: The Commerce Department issues Retail Sales for July.
0830/1230: The USDA releases weekly Export Sales.
1000/1400: The Commerce Department issues Business Inventories for June.
1000/1400: Freddie Mac issues weekly U.S. mortgage rates.
1030/1430: EIA issues weekly U.S. underground natural gas stocks.
1100/1500: The Treasury Department weekly announcement of 3- and 6-month bill sale offerings; and announces sales of 52-week bills and 5-year Treasury Inflation-Protected Securities.
1100/1500: The Federal Reserve Bank of Kansas City issues Labor Market Conditions Index for July.
1300/1700: The Treasury Dept. sells 30-year bonds.
1600/2000: USDA issues weekly world cotton price.
After 1600/2000: The Investment Company Institute issues weekly money market mutual fund data.
1630/2030: The Federal Reserve releases weekly balance sheet.
